  "text": "The starting point for any computer investigation needs to be an analysis of log files in the system. Syslog is designed to provide the ability to report system events.Log files on Linux systems are interesting things. They are highly configurable, efficient and detailed. Linux logs are in clear text, so you will not need to use any third-party software or utilities to perform effective searches [5] . The data passed by the syslogd daemon to a remote syslogd process is sent in clear text [CITATION_1] . It is observable using a network analysis tool such as tcpdump. This allows an invader to view the events being reported by routers or switches and by tools such as Snort5. The invader can then use this information to determine which systems they need to attack. So the problem in syslog is that it lacks confidentiality.",
